Need a wine suggestion for the holidays? How about these two — 
/* 
Bodegas Protos Reserva 2015. 100% Tempranillo.  Hand harvested from 50 year old vineyards.  Aged for 18 months in 80% French and 20% American oak barrels, followed by 24 months in bottle.  Deep Cherry color with garnet rim, Intense nose of black fruit, licorice with lightly toasted vanilla, sweet spice, mineral and balsamic notes. Good acidity with a balance of fruit and oak characteristics.  Long and harmonious finish.  Roast beef, lamb or turkey, casseroles, baked ham, charcuterie, cured cheeses, savory tarts.
/* 
Bodegas Protos Gran Reserva 2015. 100% Tempranillo.  Hand harvested from 60 year old vineyards.  Aged for 18 months in 80% French and 20% American oak barrels, followed by 36 months in bottle.  Deep Cherry color with garnet rim. Expressive and complex nose of mature fruits, cocoa, tobacco, mineral notes, toffee, and smoky hints.  Round tannins with good aging potential.  Long luxuriant finish.  Roast beef, lamb or turkey, casseroles, charcuterie, mature cured cheeses, savory tarts.  Rich chocolate desserts. 
/*
/* 
