Maita & I recently enjoyed an evening with Bodega Colomé winemaker Thibaut Delmotte in an exclusive wine and tapas tasting at the Proper Hotel DTLA, Cara Cara Rooftop Restaurant.  Such a pleasure to meet and talk wine with Thibaut Delmotte, and taste his line of Malbec! What beautiful wines!  Also thanks to Lori @lorilynnpr & Kyle @kyleakaplan for including us at this fun event.  BTW the tapas & desserts were amazing!  Sorry, no pics, too busy eating everything lol — 
/*
/* 
Colomé Estate Torrontes, my first time trying this varietal, and I loved it. Very aromatic, with nice acidity and smooth texture.
/* 
Colomé Estate Malbec  A blend of 4 vineyards from multiple elevations from 5,500 ft to 10,200 ft. (1,700 meters, 2,300, 2,600, & 3,111). Dark fruit, floral notes, big and bold.
/* 
Colome Authentico Malbec.  From the best vineyards at 7,500 ft (2,300 meters). Dark fruit, clove, and spice.  They use no oak in this one.  10 mos in tank, 10 mos in bottle. 
/* 
Colome El Arenal Malbec.  High altitude single vineyard, 8,500 ft (2,600 meters). Dark fruit, freshness, power, complexity, and elegance. 
/* 
Colomé 1831.  This is from the home vineyard planted in 1831. Vines over 100 years old, at an altitude of 7500 ft (2,300 meters). A beautiful wine.  Dark fruit, floral, and spice notes, elegant and complex.  I need some of these for sure.
/*
/* 
