Our first time at Etta @ettarestaurant_la in Culver City.  It was just the 2 of us so we couldn’t try as many things as we wanted to.  Next time coming with another couple or 2.  We started with a glass of the Victorine de Chastenay Cremant Rose along with the chilled oysters.  Then ordered a caesar salad and their amazing 40 oz bone-in-hearth-roasted short rib.  It’s served with several condiments along with lettuce for making lettuce wraps & naan and all that just adds to that delicious short rib.  Next time we will try the pizza and pasta. 
