Clos Triguedina is a family-owned winery located in Cahors, France. It has been in operation for over 190 years and is known for its production of Malbec wines. The winery is located on a 70-hectare estate that is planted with vines that are over 30+ years old, on soil of limestone & clay & siliceous clay, similar to that of the famed Pomerol region.  Winemaker and proprietor Jean-Luc Baldes.
/*
The name Clos Triguedina “Me Trigo de Dina” means “Longing to Dine” in the ancient Occitane, and this name is reflected in this classic Clos Triguedina cuvee.
/*
I enjoyed the 2020 Clos Triguedina Petit Clos, 85% Malbec,15% Merlot. Made for early drinking but can age nicely for 5 to 8 years.  Nice dark fruit, soft tannins, and well balanced.
/*
And also enjoyed the 2020 Clos Triguedina Cuvee, 85% Malbec, 10% Merlot, 5% Tannat.  A solid Malbec, built to age, too young right now but 5 to 10 years it will be beautiful. Check them out! —  Paired with some amazing pizza made by Matt the Master Pizzaman @cheungmc — 
