A Negroni is an Italian cocktail, one part gin, one part vermouth rosso (red, semi sweet) and one part Campari, garnished with orange peel. Usually stirred, not shaken. Story has it that it was created in the early 1900's by Count Camillo Negroni. He asked the bartender to strengthen his favorite cocktail, the Americano, with gin instead of club soda.
