Jean-Marc Pillot is a highly respected winemaker in Burgundy, France. He is known for his elegant and complex white wines, made from Chardonnay grapes. Pillot's wines are typically aged in a mix of new and old oak barrels, which gives them a balance of richness and freshness. 
