4G Wine is a South African wine estate founded by Philipp G. Axt. — Marketing Director, Vanessa Bouwman-Axt, Winemaker, Dr Valerie Lavigne. 4G Wine is still a young estate, but it has already made a name for itself for its production of high-quality wines — The last photo is with Philipp & Vanessa — 
/* 
Wednesday night 9/27 was their intimate launch event for the G. 2017 Zwizzirōn, Bordeaux style red (Cab, Cab Franc, Syrah, Petit Verdot), at the Michelin Star - Plumed Horse, Saratoga CA — 
/* 
The name ZWIZZIRŌN is the original Proto-West Germanic word which means “to twitter”, a short burst of inconsequential information, a high-pitched chirp from a bird. — 
/* 
2017 was the year when social media most prominently took over a huge proportion of communication throughout the world. Every single person could be an even more or less convincing sender of information, to be heard by millions and millions of people, and it even manifested itself as an official channel more than ever in the world of politics, and global discourse. Little stories compressed into 140 characters with big impact. — 
/* 
The G. 2017 label is a dedication to this crazy wonderworld of communication, the chaotic and complex cacophony of messages being chirped from all these little birds from all over the world, creating followers and influencing society and movements. — These are the most incredible labels, under a black light the label comes to life! 
/* 
