Produced by the renowned Champagne house Henri Giraud. Made from 90% Pinot Noir and 10% Chardonnay grapes, sourced from the Ay Grand Cru, a prestigious vineyard within the Champagne region known for producing exceptional Pinot Noir grapes. They use a unique production method where the grapes ferment entirely in oak barrels, unlike most rosé Champagnes which are made by blending red and white wines. This gives the 2012 Rosé Argonne a distinct character and complexity.
/* 
